testterminal

Print a visual test pattern for the current terminal: the full
256-color ANSI palette (each cell shown as both a background swatch
and the matching foreground number), followed by a sample line of
text rendered in regular, bold, italic, bold-italic, underline,
strikethrough, and red.

Useful for sanity-checking terminal color/font configuration and for
spotting ambiguous glyphs in a font (`O0 l1 Z2 S5 G6 B8` etc.).
